<span style='float: right; width: 280px; height: 187px; margin: 0 0 5px 5px; border: 1px solid black;'><script type='text/javascript'>flash_object ('http://graphics.millsberry.com/buddy/buddy_featured.swf', '280', '187', 'userName=pukgi&buddyTimeStamp=20050425&buddyScriptURL=http%3A%2F%2Fmillsberry.com%2Fbuddy%2Fload_buddy_xml.phtml&unixTimeStamp=1193060247&serverTimeOffset=28800', '', 'exactfit', 'transparent');</script></span>
Meet <b>Pukgi</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>Pukgi lives at <a href='/home/?user=pukgi'>26034 Cherry Blossom Stree</a>t, in the old, historical neighborhood of Ravenwood.  He has been a citizen since January 15, 2005, and he's really enjoying his time here.<br><br>Pukgi is well-known at Millsberry Academy for his great sporting skills.  Those who know him best speak of the many trophies he has earned from such activities as Sink the Three, Rope Race, and Home Run Derby.  You can usually find this athletic guy after school, dribbling a basketball and ready for a friendly game of one-on-one against anyone who wants to play.  Though he loves many different kinds of sports, Pukgi's favorite is football.  When football season arrives, Pukgi's black elbow pads and the lucky violet and green wristbands he wears during games make him easy to spot!<br><br>When Pukgi's not actively playing a sport, he likes to have some quiet time to himself.  Most of the time, he will crack open a book and read about some of his favorite subjects.  Since animals are a primary interest of his, Pukgi is often found browsing through the Millsberry Academy Library's animal books.  At other times, Pukgi likes to put some pop, modern rock, or soft rock on his stereo, then lie back on his bed and just think about things.<br><br>Due to his friendly nature, Pukgi spends a good deal of his time with his friends, often at either his best friend's house or Peabody Park.  There, they like to hang out and talk about everything from athletics to zoology.  On occasion, if the weather is nice, Pukgi and his buddies will square off for an informal game of touch football.  <br><br>However, Pukgi doesn't spend all his time in Peabody Park playing sports.  You can also find him from time to time, walking along the grass while carefully picking up trash from the ground.  Additionally, Pukgi has also helped out the Millsberry Police with tracking down their most wanted criminals, showing that he is certainly a supportive member of the community.<br><br>Thank you for being a fine citizen, Pukgi, and congratulations on being named Millsberry's citizen of the week!</div>
